    StoryV2("S130", "dp-runtime: FastAPI skeleton + /healthz with version+commit", "S3", "E1", 1, "P0", "AC: GET /healthz returns 200 with {version, commit_sha, db_ok}. [extends S008/S012]", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass7 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/observability/structured-logging.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/healthz.py — sibling to cp-api healthz, narrower probe set (db/cp_api/otel). build_runtime_healthz returns RuntimeHealth where db_ok=False ⇒ status=unhealthy (load balancer takes the pod out), cp_api or otel down ⇒ degraded (still serves). Async probes called via _safe_probe so any exception flips ok→False rather than crashing the route. Tests: default green path, otel-down maps to degraded with otel_ok=False. Open questions: db probe in production uses a pinned 'SELECT 1' query bound to the dp-runtime pgbouncer pool — wired in the route handler, not in this module."),
    StoryV2("S131", "dp-runtime: Pydantic Settings for LOOP_RUNTIME_*", "S3", "E1", 1, "P0", "AC: missing-required raises at startup; values match ENV_REFERENCE.md §2.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/settings.py — Settings(BaseSettings) with env_prefix='LOOP_RUNTIME_', extra='forbid'; SecretStr for paseto_key; Literal for environment ('dev'|'staging'|'prod') and log_format ('json'|'console'); HttpUrl for cp_api_url + otel_endpoint; bounded turn_default_timeout_ms / per-workspace concurrency / per-workspace+per-agent RPS. load_settings(**overrides) for tests. Tests: defaults, env overrides, extra-fields rejected, port bounds, invalid environment Literal, SecretStr redacted in repr. Open questions: pydantic-settings already pinned in runtime pyproject from S101 work."),
    StoryV2("S132", "dp-runtime: cp-api client (workspace+agent+version lookup with cache)", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: get_agent_config(workspace_id, agent_id) hits cp-api, caches 60s; cache invalidation on 404.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass4 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T03:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/cp_client.py — TtlCache with single-flight get_or_fetch() coalescing concurrent fetches, asyncio.Lock-guarded, bounded max_entries with O(n) closest-to-expiry eviction. CpApiFetcher Protocol abstracts transport; CpApiClient.workspace()/agent_version() each have their own TtlCache so eviction pressure is independent. WorkspaceRecord/AgentVersionRecord are pydantic v2 strict models. Tests: TTL hit/miss, single-flight under 10 concurrent callers, per-record-type cache isolation. Open questions: 60s TTL configurable via cp-api settings; 404-invalidation will hook .invalidate() in the http error mapper (next slice)."),
    StoryV2("S133", "dp-runtime: workspace-context middleware sets loop.workspace_id GUC", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: after middleware, RLS-protected reads in handlers see only that workspace's rows; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass4 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T03:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/workspace_context.py — frozen WorkspaceContext (workspace_id, user_sub, request_id) + ContextVar holder + use_workspace() async context manager. current_workspace() raises WorkspaceContextError outside a block so missing pin is loud. Tests: pin-during-block, raise-outside-block, concurrent-task isolation (two coroutines see their own pin). Open questions: actually setting the postgres `loop.workspace_id` GUC is a per-connection SET LOCAL the data-plane SQLAlchemy session does on checkout — wired in the persistence slice (S137 family); this story lands the contextvar plumbing the SQL hook reads from."),
    StoryV2("S134", "dp-runtime: API-key auth middleware (calls cp-api /verify)", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: valid key → workspace_id; invalid → 401 LOOP-RT-101; cache 60s; cache busted on revoke event.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass4 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/security/secret-handling.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T03:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/auth.py — ApiKeyVerifier hashes presented key with sha256, queries KeyDirectory Protocol (production = httpx call to cp-api /verify), returns ApiKeyClaim(workspace_id, user_sub, issued_at_ms). Positive-only caching with TTL; negative results never cached to avoid timing oracles on cache fill. hmac.compare_digest belt-and-braces equality. invalidate(plaintext) hook is what the revoke-event consumer wires up. Tests: known-hash accepted + cached, empty key rejected, unknown key rejected, runtime_checkable Protocol verified. Open questions: revoke-event topic shape under S116/S134 alignment."),
    StoryV2("S135", "dp-runtime: POST /v1/turns accepts AgentEvent and returns SSE TurnEvent stream", "S3", "E1", 3, "P0", "AC: client posts AgentEvent, receives token + tool_call + complete frames; backpressure-safe.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass8 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/api/streaming-sse.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/sse.py — SseEncoder framing for /v1/turns. SseEventKind {TURN_EVENT, DONE, ERROR, KEEPALIVE}; SseFrame.to_bytes() emits 4-line wire format \"event:<k>\\nid:<n>\\ndata:<json>\\n\\n\". encode_turn_event(turn_event)/encode_done(turn_id)/encode_error(code,message)/encode_keepalive helpers each bump a monotonic id counter so stream consumers can resume on reconnect. JSON serialization uses sort_keys=True so wire bytes are byte-stable for replay. Tests: encoder bumps id, framing matches the `event:`/`id:`/`data:`/blank-line shape, error frame carries code+message, keepalive emits no data payload. Open questions: backpressure budget (max-frames-per-second) deferred to S141 e2e harness."),
    StoryV2("S136", "dp-runtime: tool registry initialization from agent_version.config_json", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: agent config lists MCP servers; runtime spins them up; tools available in TurnExecutor.execute.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass4 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T03:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/tool_registry.py — build_registry(config_json, factories) parses config_json[tools]=[{name,config}], looks up factory per name, instantiates each (sync or async factory), returns a registry exposing get(name)/names()/__contains__ — exactly the surface TurnExecutor consumes. Validation rejects malformed entries, duplicate names, unknown names, non-dict configs; factory exceptions are wrapped in ToolRegistryInitError so the runtime gets a uniform failure mode. Tests: build-from-config, unknown-tool rejected, duplicate-name rejected, no-tools-key tolerated. Open questions: MCP-server lifecycle (start/stop) is the factory's concern; this slice intentionally does not own process management."),
    StoryV2("S137", "dp-runtime: persistence: insert turns row + tool_calls rows on TurnEvent close", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: after complete, SELECT count(*) FROM turns WHERE conversation_id=$1 grows by 1; tool_calls grows by N.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass7 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/data/migrations-and-rls.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/turn_persistence.py — TurnPersistence.persist_complete(turn, tool_calls) idempotent on turn_id; re-applying an identical PersistedTurn returns False (no-op), divergent re-apply raises TurnPersistenceError so retry loops cannot silently overwrite. tool_call rows whose turn_id mismatches the parent are rejected. select_count_query() returns the parametrised SQL the integration test runs ('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM turns WHERE workspace_id=:ws AND conversation_id=:conv'). InMemoryTurnSink for unit tests; Postgres adapter wraps single SQL transaction. Tests: idempotent re-apply, divergent re-apply raises, tool_call turn_id mismatch raises, count_query is parametrised. Open questions: the SQL adapter using SQLAlchemy lives behind a feature flag pending pgbouncer pool config story."),
    StoryV2("S138", "dp-runtime: graceful shutdown drains in-flight turns up to 30s", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: SIGTERM → server stops accepting; in-flight stream completes; readiness flips false; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass4 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/ops/graceful-shutdown.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T03:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/shutdown.py — GracefulShutdown.register(turn_id, task) tracks in-flight asyncio.Task handles with auto-cleanup via add_done_callback. .shutdown(deadline_s=30) flips shutting_down (rejects new register), waits with asyncio.wait(ALL_COMPLETED, timeout), cancels any still-running and awaits cancellations, returns DrainResult(drained, cancelled, elapsed_s). max_inflight is an optional admission cap. Tests: drain happy path, deadline-cancellation, post-shutdown register raises ShutdownError. Open questions: SIGTERM handler + readiness-probe wiring is the FastAPI lifespan (next slice); this story lands the orchestrator the lifespan calls."),
    StoryV2("S139", "dp-runtime: per-workspace + per-agent rate limit", "S3", "E1", 2, "P0", "AC: cap configurable; 429 LOOP-RT-301 with retry-after; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass4 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/api/rate-limit.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T03:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/turn_rate_limit.py — TurnRateLimiter composes two RateLimiter instances (S117): workspace-coarse and per-agent slice. .admit(workspace_id, agent_id, cost) enforces both tiers and returns TurnRateLimitDecision(admitted, workspace_ok, agent_ok, reason) — workspace_budget_exceeded short-circuits before the agent debit; agent_budget_exceeded surfaced separately so retry-after picks the right tier. Tests: both-tiers admit until agent cap, workspace-block short-circuits before agent, decision.reason maps to LOOP-RT-301 vendor. Open questions: workspace-token over-debit on agent reject is bounded by refill_per_sec — we accept the tiny inflation rather than complicate atomic-rollback; documented in module docstring."),
