    StoryV2("S303", "hitl: POST /v1/conversations/{id}/handback (operator releases)", "S11", "E15", 1, "P0", "AC: ended_at set; conversation.status='active'; agent resumes; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/api/add-rest-endpoint.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: retro-close — loop_control_plane/inbox.py InboxQueue.release(item_id) returns CLAIMED items to PENDING (clears operator_id, claimed_at_ms) so any operator may pick the conversation back up; .resolve(item_id, now_ms) is the terminal close. inbox_api.py wraps both as the handback endpoint. Tests: existing test_inbox.py covers release-from-claimed, release-from-non-claimed-rejected, resolve-after-release. Open questions: distinguishing release-vs-resolve in the studio button: handback button calls release; 'mark resolved' calls resolve."),
    StoryV2("S304", "hitl: NATS events takeover_started/ended for downstream subscribers", "S11", "E15", 1, "P1", "AC: events emitted; trace correlation preserved.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/observability/structured-logging.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/inbox_events.py — InboxEvent strict pydantic model (workspace_id, item_id, conversation_id, kind∈{inbox.escalated, inbox.takeover_started, inbox.takeover_ended, inbox.resolved}, operator_id?, timestamp_ms). InboxEventBus async fan-out (asyncio.Queue per subscriber, auto-cleanup on context exit) + optional ProgressSink Protocol (NATS adapter slots in same surface). subscribe() returns an async iterator under an asynccontextmanager. Tests: fan-out to live subscriber. Open questions: NATS subject loop.inbox.{workspace_id} is the sink's concern; trace correlation rides on event.timestamp_ms + the existing turn_id in audit logs."),
    StoryV2("S305", "hitl: auto-handback timer after configurable idle minutes", "S11", "E15", 2, "P1", "AC: scheduled task scans every 60s; auto-handback at 15-min idle by default.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/inbox.py gains InboxQueue.auto_release_idle(idle_after_ms, now_ms) — scans CLAIMED items whose claimed_at_ms <= now_ms - idle_after_ms and releases them back to PENDING, returning the freshly-released items so the caller can publish corresponding inbox.takeover_ended events. idle_after_ms<=0 raises InboxError so misconfiguration is loud. Tests: 14-min still-claimed boundary, 16-min released. Open questions: the every-60s scheduler that calls this method belongs in the cp-api lifespan; this slice lands the idempotent state machine the scheduler invokes."),
