    StoryV2("S320", "billing: cp-api → Stripe customer creation on workspace POST", "S12", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: stripe.Customer.create called with workspace metadata; customer_id stored. [extends S025]", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass7 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/security/zero-trust.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: retro-close — loop_control_plane/billing.py exposes BillingClient Protocol with create_customer(workspace_id, email) -> StripeCustomer plus FakeBillingClient for tests. The cloud-portability constraint forbids importing the stripe-python SDK directly (pinned in the module docstring); the production adapter that wraps stripe.Customer.create lives in a separate module and is selected via dependency injection. customer_id is stored on the workspace row by the cp-api workspace-create handler. The webhook handler in stripe_webhook.py reverses the lookup. Tests: existing test_billing.py covers create_customer/get_customer/get_subscription roundtrips. Open questions: idempotency-key wiring on retries is a follow-up resilience story."),
