    StoryV2("S322", "billing: Stripe webhook receiver /v1/billing/webhook (signature verified)", "S12", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: invalid sig → 400 LOOP-BIL-101; valid → handlers dispatch.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/security/secret-handling.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/stripe_webhook.py — verify_signature() re-implements Stripe's t=<ts>,v1=<sig> header check (HMAC-SHA256 over `${ts}.${rawBody}`, hmac.compare_digest, 5-min default tolerance) without importing the stripe SDK so the cp stays cloud-portable. StripeWebhookDispatcher composes verification with handler dispatch and dedupes by event.id (retry-idempotent). Tests: signature round-trip, tampered-payload rejected, stale-timestamp rejected, dispatcher de-dupes on retry. Open questions: stripe-python adapter that pushes the raw body into dispatch lives in the cp-api FastAPI route, outside this generic module."),
    StoryV2("S323", "billing: handle customer.subscription.created/updated/deleted", "S12", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: workspace.plan kept in sync with active subscription; downgrade enforced.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/security/secret-handling.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/stripe_webhook.py parse_subscription_event(event) — returns frozen SubscriptionChange(customer_id, subscription_id, status, plan_id?) extracting plan_id from items.data[0].price.id with defensive isinstance checks; raises StripeWebhookError if customer/id/status missing. The application registers a handler via dispatcher.on('customer.subscription.updated', ...) (and .created/.deleted) that calls WorkspaceService to flip workspace.plan; downgrade enforcement piggybacks on the existing PlanLimitGuard since the next admit() will see the new plan. Tests: dispatcher routes a sub.updated event into a handler that captures status='active', idempotent retry suppressed. Open questions: plan-id→tier mapping (price_pro_monthly→pro) is workspace-config; Plan.tier names must align with stripe price metadata."),
    StoryV2("S324", "billing: handle invoice.paid / payment_failed events", "S12", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: paid → workspace.payment_status='ok'; failed N times → suspend workspace.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/security/secret-handling.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/stripe_webhook.py parse_invoice_event(event) — returns frozen InvoiceOutcome(customer_id, invoice_id, paid, amount_paid_micro, attempt_count); cents→micro-USD conversion (x10_000) so amounts speak the same units as cost_rollup. Application handler on 'invoice.paid' clears payment_status; on 'invoice.payment_failed' increments attempt_count and once it crosses N (default 3) calls SuspensionService.suspend(reason='payment_failed'). Tests: invoice.paid handler captures cents→micro conversion (1234c → 12_340_000µUSD). Open questions: N=3 retry threshold is a workspace-tier policy — hobby could be 1 attempt, enterprise could be 7; configurable in subsequent slice."),
    StoryV2("S325", "billing: nightly usage push from ClickHouse → Stripe metered", "S12", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: scheduled job reads usage_events deltas, calls stripe.UsageRecord.create; idempotent on retry.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass10 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/data/event-streaming.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/billing_export.py UsageWindow validators + UsageQuantity + idempotency_key(workspace,metric,window) + StripeMeteredClient/UsageAggregator Protocols + yesterday_window_utc 24h midnight-aligned + DEFAULT_METRIC_NAMES. Tests: test_billing_export_pass10.py. Open questions: none."),
    StoryV2("S326", "billing: workspace-suspension middleware (read-only when suspended)", "S12", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: suspended workspace cannot create runs; returns 402 LOOP-BIL-301.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass5 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/api/add-rest-endpoint.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-12T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_control_plane/suspension.py — SuspensionService.suspend(reason∈{payment_failed, manual, tos_violation}) is idempotent (second call keeps original since_ms so the user sees the original suspension time). .check_writeable(workspace_id) raises WorkspaceSuspendedError with structured (workspace_id, reason, since_ms) which the error mapper translates to 402 LOOP-BIL-301. Reads remain unblocked so the user can navigate billing UI to fix payment. Tests: suspend→write blocked, idempotent suspend keeps original since_ms, reinstate restores write access. Open questions: SuspensionRecord persistence — currently in-memory; the workspaces.suspended_at column is the production backing."),
