    StoryV2("S388", "voice: cost-tracking per voice call (ASR sec, TTS sec, LLM tokens)", "S15", "E19", 2, "P0", "AC: usage_events row per call; visible in cost dashboard.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass7 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/observability/structured-logging.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_voice/voice_cost.py — VoiceCallCostAggregator(workspace_id, call_id, rates=VoiceCostRates(...)) accumulates asr_seconds, tts_seconds, carrier_seconds, llm_tokens_in, llm_tokens_out via add_* methods (negative inputs raise ValueError at the boundary). finalize() emits a frozen VoiceCallCostEvent with cost_usd_micro computed entirely in integer micro-USD (asr/tts/carrier billed per minute, LLM per 1k tokens) — no float drift across rollups. Default rates: $0.016/min ASR, $0.012/min TTS, $0.013/min carrier, $0.0005/1k tokens-in, $0.0015/1k tokens-out. Total of multiple events via VoiceCallCostAggregator.total_cost_micro for monthly rollup. Wires into the existing usage-event pipeline (S281). Tests: rollup math matches expected micro-USD for a 60s ASR + 30s TTS + 60s carrier + 2k/1k tokens call, negative inputs rejected, total_cost_micro aggregates events. Open questions: per-tenant override of VoiceCostRates is wired via WorkspaceSettings in a follow-up story."),
    StoryV2("S389", "voice: graceful degrade on provider outage (fallback ASR/TTS)", "S15", "E7", 2, "P1", "AC: primary fails -> secondary picks up within 1s; audible indicator on quality drop.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass8 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/architecture/failover.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_voice/provider_failover.py — ProviderEntry(id, call) + ProviderFailover(providers, failure_threshold=3, cooldown_seconds=30.0). ProviderState {HEALTHY, UNHEALTHY, COOLDOWN} per provider. .call(*args, now_fn=, **kwargs) tries entries in order; per-call success resets consecutive_failures, failure increments and trips to UNHEALTHY at threshold. After cooldown_seconds the entry transitions to COOLDOWN (eligible again). Exhaustion raises ProviderFailoverExhausted(attempted: tuple[str], last_error). Duplicate provider ids rejected at construction. Tests: primary success, primary-fail->fallback, threshold trips state to UNHEALTHY, cooldown reactivates, exhaustion carries attempted+last_error, empty/duplicate rejected. Open questions: audible quality-drop indicator is an upstream UX cue rendered by the TTS gateway, not the failover layer."),

