    StoryV2("S400", "multi: AgentGraph type + Pydantic schema (nodes, edges, conditions)", "S16", "E14", 2, "P0", "AC: schema validates 3 hand-written graphs; round-trip JSON. [extends S038/S042]", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/data/strict-pydantic-models.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: packages/runtime/loop_runtime/agent_graph.py — pydantic v2 strict-frozen models AgentNode (input_template, output_key, agent_id+version, timeout_ms), ParallelOperator (branch_node_ids, reducer kind), TerminalNode, Edge (from_id, to_id, optional condition); AgentGraph(nodes 2..64, edges, entry_id, loop_bound 1..64) with model_validator(after) enforcing unique ids, entry-in-nodes, ≥1 terminal, edge endpoints valid, and reachability that treats ParallelOperator.branch_node_ids as virtual fan-out edges so parallel branches do not need to sit on the parent's edge list. helpers outgoing()/get_node(). Tests: duplicate-id rejected, unreachable-node rejected, terminal-required, plus the executor's pattern-builder tests round-trip three hand-written graphs (supervisor, pipeline, parallel). Open questions: yaml flow→graph compiler (S409) sits one level up."),
    StoryV2("S401", "multi: Supervisor pattern impl (one supervisor delegates to N workers)", "S16", "E14", 2, "P0", "AC: supervisor calls workers in sequence; aggregates results; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/agent_patterns.build_supervisor(supervisor, workers, reducer, output_key, loop_bound) emits supervisor → __fanout__ (ParallelOperator with workers as branch_node_ids) → __end__. Reducer choices first_non_empty / concat_text / join_outputs / max_score; default max_score (longest non-empty) is the supervisor's pick-the-best heuristic. Validates ≥1 worker and no id collision with the supervisor. Tests in _tests/test_agent_graph.py: supervisor delegates to 3 workers, concat_text reducer joins outputs in declaration order, max_score picks the longest reply, supervisor output flows into worker prompts via {task} template. Open questions: streaming-aggregation vs full-collect is a reducer-flag deferred to S407."),
    StoryV2("S402", "multi: Pipeline pattern impl (linear chain with shared state)", "S16", "E14", 2, "P0", "AC: each node receives previous output; failure halts; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/agent_patterns.build_pipeline(steps, output_key, loop_bound) emits a single linear chain step[0]→step[1]→…→step[n-1]→__end__ with the terminal exposing the last step's output_key (overridable). Each step writes its output into the shared state dict under step.output_key; subsequent steps reference it via {step_a} format placeholders in their input_template. Failures bubble out of the executor (no retry semantics by design). Tests: 3-stage pipeline runs in order, each step prompt formed from the previous step's output, terminal output equals the last step's output. Open questions: per-step retry policy belongs in agent_version config not in the pattern builder."),
    StoryV2("S403", "multi: Parallel pattern impl (fan-out / fan-in with reducer)", "S16", "E14", 2, "P0", "AC: N parallel calls; reducer combines; first-to-finish-wins option; integration test.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/agent_patterns.build_parallel(branches≥2, reducer, output_key, loop_bound) emits ParallelOperator-as-entry → __end__ with branches as branch_node_ids. ParallelOperator runs all branches via asyncio.gather; each branch executes in a fresh _RunCtx (state and counts copies) so branches can't observe each other's writes. Reducer first_non_empty fulfils 'first-to-finish-wins' semantics (first branch with non-empty output wins); concat_text/join_outputs/max_score cover combine flavours. Tests: first_non_empty skips blank branch and surfaces the second's output, isolation enforced by per-branch state copies, executor's invoke_parallel verified separately. Open questions: literal first-result-cancels-others is a follow-up flag on the operator."),
    StoryV2("S404", "multi: AgentGraph executor (DFS over nodes, condition eval)", "S16", "E14", 3, "P0", "AC: executes any valid graph end-to-end; tools invoked per-node; result merged.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/graph_executor.GraphExecutor(invoker).run(graph, initial_state) walks the graph DFS-style: AgentNode → format_map(state) prompt + asyncio.wait_for(invoke, timeout_ms) + state[output_key]=result; ParallelOperator → asyncio.gather over per-branch _RunCtx copies + reducer; TerminalNode → return result. Edge selection picks the first edge whose condition is None or evaluates true under the regex DSL `key == 'literal'` / `key != 42` (string + numeric literals). AgentInvoker is a Protocol so production wiring (TurnExecutor + tools) and test fakes share the surface. ExecutionResult(output, trace, state) is frozen. Tests: pipeline+supervisor+parallel happy paths, condition-based routing happy/sad branches, missing template key raises GraphRuntimeError with the exact key. Open questions: tool invocation lives in the AgentInvoker callee (TurnExecutor); the executor stays transport-agnostic."),
    StoryV2("S405", "multi: cycle detection at compile + safe-loop-bounds at runtime", "S16", "E14", 2, "P0", "AC: cyclic graph allowed only when max_iterations bounded; uncapped raises.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass6 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/coding/python-package-layout.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-19T04:00:00Z. Substance: graph_executor.detect_cycles(graph) Tarjan SCC walk returns components-of-size>1 plus self-loops; AgentGraph.loop_bound (1..64, default 8) caps how many times any single node may execute in one run; the executor increments a Counter per node entry and raises LoopBoundExceeded(node_id, bound) before the (bound+1)th invocation. Cyclic graphs are *allowed* (e.g. retry loops with edge-condition exit) provided loop_bound caps blast radius. Tests: detect_cycles finds two-node SCC, returns empty for acyclic, LoopBoundExceeded raised when self-loop with always-true condition exceeds bound=3. Open questions: per-node max_iterations override (vs graph-wide bound) lands when retry-loops in the wild demand finer control."),
