    StoryV2("S407", "multi: cost rollup across sub-agents into parent turn", "S16", "E2", 1, "P0", "AC: parent.cost_usd = sum(child.cost_usd); usage_events tagged with parent_turn_id.", owner="GitHub Copilot", status="Done", notes_override="Done. Branch: copilot/s-pass7 (merged). PR: local-merge (ff to main). Skill: skills/observability/structured-logging.md. Last step: 5/5. Heartbeat: 2026-05-26T04:00:00Z. Substance: loop_runtime/multi_agent_cost.py — MultiAgentCostRollup.aggregate(parent, children) returns RollupResult(parent_cost_usd_micro, children_cost_usd_micro, total_cost_usd_micro, parent_tokens_in/out, total_tokens_in/out, child_breakdown). Validation: parent must have parent_turn_id=None, every child must have parent_turn_id == parent.turn_id (raise ValueError otherwise) — guarantees we cannot accidentally roll up cross-parent traffic. All cost values stored as int micro-USD; .total_cost_usd convenience reads back as float. child_breakdown is a tuple of frozen rows so the result is hashable and safe to stash in a trace. Tests: parent+2-child aggregation sums correctly, parent with parent_turn_id rejected, child mismatched parent_turn_id rejected. Open questions: ClickHouse mat-view aggregating these results lives in S281's ops follow-up."),
